                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">1) Why is the US allowed nukes, but iraq isn't.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />We have had nukes for a long time, and currently keep them as a defesive mesure.  Iraq is a provenly ofensive nation.  The cold war was bad enugh when it was two (or more, but mainly 2) realitivly large defensive nations standing off, adding offensive nations to that would be a bad idea.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">2) If as bush says this is to liberate the iraqi people, why not attack Israel? India?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />clarify what point you are trying to make here, I will not assume to know what you are asking.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">3) Sadam is being attacked for "supposedly" having weapons. WW2, we KNEW hitler had weapons, and it took 2 years for the US to enter it...<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />US had a policy of utter indererance reguarding nations outside of direct contact to the US at that time.  It would have taken us longer than that to enter into that war had a nation not attacked us.  I do honestly think we should have gotten involved in that war much earlier, but that of course is from a hindsight view where I know exactly what hitler was doing with his PoW's and Jews.<br />Taken from the point of view as an average american during the start of world war II, I would fully agree with going to the defense of nations attacked, but would debate our right to upsure germany rightfully elected leader.<br /><br />Of course had we gotten involved earlier things might have been quite different, for one we probly would not have attacked japan first, probly prefering to come to the aid of eruope.  having troops in europe would have delayed hitlers advancement, yet leave us less defended in the pacific.  with japan coming at, and our military divided, who knows what might have happend.<br /><br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11832" target="_blank"><img src="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/pic.jpg" border="0"></a><br /><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/topless.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic R</a></center></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
